[3] Montana (Lake County/Flathead Reservation)
Date: Wed 22 May 2019
Source: KULR8 [edited]
https://www.kulr8.com/regional/pertussis-cases-in-lake-co-grow-to-includes-infants/article_402d9020-54ba-5d3b-ac98-4bfdcde7b99b.html


The number of whooping cough cases in Lake County has now grown to 19, and health officials said on Wednesday [22 May 2019] that 4 of the cases are infants.

The following post is from the Lake County Public Health Facebook page:

Lake County/Flathead Reservation has bumped up to 19 confirmed pertussis cases. The outbreak is now considered to be community-wide.

Ages: [less than] 1 year = 4 [cases] (3 weeks, 1 month, 3 months, 7 months); 1-4 years = 5 [cases]; 5-10 years = 6 [cases]; and [greater than] 10 years = 4 [cases].

Vaccination status: unvaccinated = 13 [cases].

[byline: Angela Marshall]

