[5] Maine (Portland)
Date: Wed 29 May 2019
Source: News Center Maine [edited]
https://www.newscentermaine.com/article/news/local/at-least-3-cases-of-whooping-cough-confirmed-at-portland-schools-but-more-likely/97-d9a45e22-0c6e-4c62-9614-3016c3b1ed1e


Portland schools confirmed 3 [4?] cases of whooping cough in the district on Wednesday [29 May 2019], but there are likely more.

Tess Nacelewicz, Communications Coordinator for Portland Public Schools, issued a statement on 29 May [2019], saying there has been one confirmed case of pertussis at Longfellow Elementary School, 2 confirmed cases at Lincoln Middle School, and one confirmed case at Deering High School. There is also a 2nd "presumed" case at Longfellow and a 3rd case "being tested" at Lincoln.

The student with pertussis from Deering has been treated with antibiotics and has since returned to school. Students in the same classes as the affected individual have not shown signs of any symptoms, and Nacelewicz says faculty is not aware of any other suspected cases at the high school.

Portland Public Schools has reported the incidents to the Maine Center for Disease Control, according to Nacelewicz. The CDC has spoken with school nursing staff, and a letter was sent to parents and staff (including custodial staff) at each school. Nacelewicz says there are no recommendations for keeping students out of schools, and though immunized students can and do contract pertussis, these infections are usually less serious.

[byline: Chloe Teboe]

