[Hauora Tairawhiti covers the same area as the Gisborne District (also known as Gisborne Region), with a population of 49 100 residents, 45% of whom are Maori; 75% of the population lives in the city of Gisborne (https://www.hauoratairawhiti.org.nz/about-us/who/tairawhiti/). Tairawhiti is said to have the highest level of economic deprivation and poorer health than any other district, contributed in part by low immunization rates (https://www.hauoratairawhiti.org.nz/about-us/who/tairawhiti/). A map showing the location of the Gisborne Region of the North Island can be found at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Island#/media/File:NZ_Territorial_Authorities_North_Island.png. - Mod.ML

